  "body": "Hi,\r\nI want to run node on different network using hardhat. My code like this:\r\n```\r\ndefaultNetwork: \"localhost\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      chainId: 31337,\r\n    },\r\n    localhost: {\r\n      chainId: 1337,\r\n      url: \"http://127.0.0.1:8545\",\r\n      accounts: privateKey !== undefined ? [privateKey] : [],\r\n    },\r\n    polygon_testnet: {\r\n      chainId: 80001,\r\n      url: polygonTestnetUrl || \"\",\r\n      accounts: privateKey !== undefined ? [privateKey] : [],\r\n    },\r\n    polygon_mainnet: {\r\n      chainId: 137,\r\n      url: polygonMainnetUrl || \"\",\r\n      accounts: privateKey !== undefined ? [privateKey] : [],\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd my package dependency like this:\r\n```\r\n\"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers\": \"2.0.4\",\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-etherscan\": \"^3.0.0\",\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-waffle\": \"^2.0.1\",\r\n    \"bip39\": \"^3.0.4\",\r\n    \"chai\": \"^4.2.0\",\r\n    \"dotenv\": \"^10.0.0\",\r\n    \"eslint\": \"^7.29.0\",\r\n    \"eslint-config-prettier\": \"^8.3.0\",\r\n    \"eslint-config-standard\": \"^16.0.3\",\r\n    \"eslint-plugin-import\": \"^2.23.4\",\r\n    \"eslint-plugin-node\": \"^11.1.0\",\r\n    \"eslint-plugin-prettier\": \"^3.4.0\",\r\n    \"eslint-plugin-promise\": \"^5.1.0\",\r\n    \"ethereum-waffle\": \"^3.0.0\",\r\n    \"ethers\": \"^5.0.0\",\r\n    \"hardhat\": \"^2.9.0\",\r\n    \"hardhat-gas-reporter\": \"^1.0.4\",\r\n    \"prettier\": \"^2.3.2\",\r\n    \"prettier-plugin-solidity\": \"^1.0.0-beta.13\",\r\n    \"solhint\": \"^3.3.6\",\r\n    \"solidity-coverage\": \"^0.7.16\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I use command \r\n```\r\nnpx hardhat node\r\n```\r\nThis run normal, but if i use command\r\n```\r\nnpx hardhat node --network localhost\r\n```\r\nReturn l error log like this\r\n```\r\nError HH605: Unsupported network for JSON-RPC server. Only hardhat is currently supported.\r\n```\r\nWhat's the matter with my code? How to fix this issue?\r\n",
